{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881813522,"sessionID":"ses_285322a00ffe9paxFH0Id3IOdd","part":{"id":"prt_d7acdfdd50010LWPZnppoBveCa","messageID":"msg_d7acdf17f001nLI2awhJihojvT","sessionID":"ses_285322a00ffe9paxFH0Id3IOdd","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-69c98a9a7da84306b62f9671a0fdcc38","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-029/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-029/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Specification\n2: \n3: ## Module: sdk-python\n4: \n5: ### HTTPClient Class\n6: \n7: #### Constructor\n8: \n9: ```python\n10: class HTTPClient:\n11:     def __init__(\n12:         self,\n13:         base_url: str,\n14:         timeout: int = 30,\n15:         max_retries: int = 3,\n16:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n17:     ) -> None\n18: ```\n19: \n20: **Parameters:**\n21: - `base_url`: Base URL of the API service\n22: - `timeout`: Request timeout in seconds (default: 30)\n23: - `max_retries`: Maximum number of retry attempts (default: 3)\n24: - `headers`: Optional default headers to include in all requests\n25: \n26: #### Core HTTP Methods\n27: \n28: ##### get\n29: \n30: ```python\n31: async def get(\n32:     self,\n33:     path: str,\n34:     params: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n35:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n36: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Parameters:**\n40: - `path`: API endpoint path\n41: - `params`: Optional query parameters\n42: - `headers`: Optional request headers\n43: \n44: **Returns:** Response data as dictionary\n45: \n46: **Raises:** `HTTPError`, `ConnectionError`, `TimeoutError`\n47: \n48: ##### post\n49: \n50: ```python\n51: async def post(\n52:     self,\n53:     path: str,\n54:     data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n55:     json: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n56:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n57: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n58: ```\n59: \n60: **Parameters:**\n61: - `path`: API endpoint path\n62: - `data`: Optional form data\n63: - `json`: Optional JSON data\n64: - `headers`: Optional request headers\n65: \n66: **Returns:** Response data as dictionary\n67: \n68: **Raises:** `HTTPError`, `ConnectionError`, `TimeoutError`, `ValidationError`\n69: \n70: ##### put\n71: \n72: ```python\n73: async def put(\n74:     self,\n75:     path: str,\n76:     data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n77:     json: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n78:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n79: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n80: ```\n81: \n82: **Parameters:**\n83: - `path`: API endpoint path\n84: - `data`: Optional form data\n85: - `json`: Optional JSON data\n86: - `headers`: Optional request headers\n87: \n88: **Returns:** Response data as dictionary\n89: \n90: **Raises:** `HTTPError`, `ConnectionError`, `TimeoutError`, `ValidationError`\n91: \n92: ##### delete\n93: \n94: ```python\n95: async def delete(\n96:     self,\n97:     path: str,\n98:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n99: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n100: ```\n101: \n102: **Parameters:**\n103: - `path`: API endpoint path\n104: - `headers`: Optional request headers\n105: \n106: **Returns:** Response data as dictionary\n107: \n108: **Raises:** `HTTPError`, `ConnectionError`, `TimeoutError`\n109: \n110: ## Data Models\n111: \n112: ### HTTPConfig\n113: \n114: ```python\n115: class HTTPConfig(BaseModel):\n116:     base_url: str\n117:     timeout: int = 30\n118:     max_retries: int = 3\n119:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n120:     verify_ssl: bool = True\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### HTTPError\n124: \n125: ```python\n126: class HTTPError(Exception):\n127:     status_code: int\n128:     message: str\n129:     details: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### RetryConfig\n133: \n134: ```python\n135: class RetryConfig(BaseModel):\n136:     max_retries: int = 3\n137:     backoff_factor: float = 1.0\n138:     retry_on_status_codes: List[int] = [429, 500, 502, 503, 504]\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ## Exception Hierarchy\n142: \n143: ```\n144: SDKHTTPException\n145: ├── HTTPError\n146: ├── ConnectionError\n147: ├── TimeoutError\n148: └── ValidationError\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ## Features\n152: \n153: ### Authentication Support\n154: - API key authentication\n155: - Bearer token authentication\n156: - Custom authentication headers\n157: \n158: ### Retry Logic\n159: - Configurable retry strategy\n160: - Exponential backoff\n161: - Status code-based retry triggers\n162: \n163: ### Error Handling\n164: - Structured error responses\n165: - Detailed error messages\n166: - Request/response logging (optional)\n167: \n168: ### Connection Pooling\n169: - Keep-alive connections\n170: - Connection limits\n171: - Timeout management\n\n(End of file - total 171 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Specification\n\n## Module: sdk-python\n\n### HTTPClient Class\n\n#### Constructor\n\n```python\nclass HTTPClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str,\n        timeout: int = 30,\n        max_retries: int = 3,\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n    ) -> None\n```\n\n**Parameters:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-029/spec.md","time":{"start":1775881813493,"end":1775881813520}}}}
